EXHIBITION INVITATION
Discover the intersection of raw material, age-old heritage, and contemporary fluid abstraction. The Raj Kishore Gupta Foundation cordially invites you to the debut public viewing of our collective master suite, showcasing a signature milestone collection curated by art critic, Uma Nair.
‘Indigenous Accents’ presents a monumental suite of contemporary abstract landscapes executed on live-edge Sheesham and Kikar wood slabs.
Pioneered by senior artist R.K. Gupta alongside his studio atelier, these works combine complex, multilayered resin pours with vibrant folk, tribal, and Aboriginal iconographies-each studied and passed down through generations.
The Details:
🗓️ Exhibition Open: July 2nd - July 6th, 2026
🥂 Official Inauguration & Reception: July 3rd,
2026 (6:30 PM onwards)
📍Venue: LTC, Bikaner House, New Delhi
